article.description: Anthony Beane scored 19 points and Southern Illinois defeated North Texas 74-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Southern Illinois defeats North Texas 74-66
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Anthony Beane scored 19 points and Southern Illinois defeated North Texas 74-66 on Saturday. Beane made three 3-pointers to help the Salukis (9-2) shoot 50 percent (9 of 18) from beyond the arc. Sean O'Brien scored 15 points with five blocked shots while Tyler Smithpeters and Rudy Stradnieks both had 11 points. J-Mychal Reese led North Texas with a career-high 25 points. Both teams struggled early, combining for eight points through the first four minutes. The Salukis went on a 13-0 run -- including a pair of 3-pointers by Smithpeters -- while Oakland (2-7) missed seven consecutive shots and five free throws. Southern Illinois led 32-18 at the break. The lead reached 20 points early in the second, but Oakland used a 17-6 run to get it back to five on Ja'Michael Brown's 3-pointer with 7:50 left. But Southern Illinois responded with back-to-back 3s by Beane and pushed its lead back to 14 with 4:07 to go.
